BCR-Jim:

Unresolved dependency: org.junit.platform junit-platform-launcherJava(0)

Look here for the workaround

[WPILib Blog] 2024 Kickoff Release of WPILib Programming
We actually have a different fix. We don’t actually have the setup in VS Code to update gradle options mid season (This is actually why the project importer exists), so we want to solve this another way. If you’re on Windows, run the following 2 commands in a Powershell Window Invoke-WebRequest -Uri https://repo.maven.apache.org/maven2/org/junit/jupiter/junit-jupiter/5.10.1/junit-jupiter-5.10.1.module -OutFile C:\Users\Public\wpilib\2024\maven\org\junit\jupiter\junit-jupiter\5.10.1\junit-jupit…

EDIT: It’s also in the official Known Issues

FIRST Robotics Competition Documentation

Known Issues

This article details known issues (and workarounds) for FRC ® Control System Software. Open Issues: Visual Studio Code Reports Unresolved Dependency: Issue: Java programs will report Unresolved dep...
